\f0\fs48 \cf2 We have developed software tools within the Semtools project that use \b \cf2 formal annotations \b0 \cf2 on environmental data to link domain-specific ontology terms from the \b \cf2 Extensible Observation Ontology (OBOE) \b0 \cf2 to particular facets of environmental data sets. This annotation approach allows us to maintain data in traditional scientific formats (e.g., CSV text, NetCDF) while still establishing formal semantics for the data. The annotations can then be used to \b \cf2 materialize a full knowledge model \b0 \cf2 of the data (e.g., an RDF graph compatible with Linked Open Data conventions), which in turn \b \cf2 drives discovery and integration \b0 \cf2 tools. \ \ We enable this through extensions to the \b \cf2 Metacat \b0 \cf2 data repository system that can be used for \b \cf2 semantic search \b0 \cf2 and \b \cf2 semantic data subsetting \b0 \cf2 for heterogeneous environmental data. The Metacat software uses the Ecological Metadata Language (EML) Data Manager Library for loading EML-described data, and incorporates the Semtools Semantic Mediation System (SMS) Java Library to enable query term expansion, semantic data subsetting, and data integration.}
